  "body": " Introduction  A measure of the goodness of an estimate is the error of estimation, the difference between the estimate and the parameter estimated (for example, the difference between and ).  We will assume throughout the remainder of this text that populations are large in comparison to the sample size and consequently that the random variables obtained through a random sample are in fact independent of one another.  "
